New Records: The starting pitcher matchup of Spencer Schwellenbach (ATL) and Simeon Woods-Richardson (MIN) was the longest-named matchup in baseball history.
Key Match Events: The Atlanta Braves beat the Minnesota Twins by a score of 8-6 in extra-innings.
Spencer Schwellenbach pitched 4.2 innings, giving up five hits and no runs, walking three and striking out eight.
Simeon Woods-Richardson pitched 4.2 innings, giving up four earned runs on three hits, walking three and striking out three.
